by Valentine Z » Sat Apr 11, 2020 12:34 am

New Spiedska wrote:One of The Chuck's most steemed allies is Port Ember, with both countries being considered "brothers-in-arms" in the world stage.

Several takes:

- The fact that women are physically stronger than men for the most parts, and on how they play a bigger role in this seemingly gender-reversed world. Not that I have issues with that, but this was something that I didn't know until now, of course. So it's unusual but a fresh breath of air to see women playing a role in music industry and the sports industry, not just the typical "Women rule the world!" It's interesting to see the society in detail, an anthropological study, shall I say!

- Which brings me to this, copying and pasting from your factbook: The music industry is notably dominated by women, with prominent heads including Rosalie Ray (Stylized as ROSA1I3), Alexa Douglas (Known professionally as Nerv-3), and Abbie Cole (Abb1). Prominent bands tend to be more focused on rock. However, notably, there are still prominent aspects of other genres (Such as synth or dubstep, among others) giving rise to an entirely new genre of music: Spiedskan. Notable contenders in this genre include the Chord Fighters, Queens Blonde, and Beyond the Beach. I wonder if Rosalie is a take on Nintendo's Rosaline, given the inspirations involved and all that. Queens Blonde seems to be a mix between Queen and Blondie... I believe.

- The fact that handball and baseball are the most popular sports, which is pretty unique on its own. Normally, I would just see football or something a bit... typical. While there is nothing with football being a national sports, it's interesting that this is probably the first time I see handball as a popular/national sports. I wonder if I will find dodgeball in their country.

Megale Calradia wrote:They're a futuristic and seemingly matristic society made up of SPLATOON PEOPLE

The several languages that made up their demographics. I would have think that an Empire, even with a good sense of unity, would have a slightly higher degree of unification after all the civil war and all that.
